    <body>
      <trans-unit id="8506" identifier="36710e8e1305fd9b7986bb20340cf7af">
        <source>Make variables called:</source>
        <target>crwdns8506:0crwdne8506:0</target>
        <note>Context: Paragraph text&#13;
XPath: /ul/li/p</note>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="8507" identifier="ca2ef64e6b857d4a4bbb8e7613c74f04">
        <source>“decimal number” and set its value to the input number given by the
end user.</source>
        <target>crwdns8507:0crwdne8507:0</target>
        <note>Context: List Item&#13;
XPath: /ul/li/ul/li</note>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="8508" identifier="1d360a2235995e46f5c3549661cd3ae2">
        <source>“bit value” and set its value to ‘32’.</source>
        <target>crwdns8508:0crwdne8508:0</target>
        <note>Context: List Item&#13;
XPath: /ul/li/ul/li[2]</note>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="8509" identifier="81789810a5e42b85e9618191672bdcfd">
        <source>Now divide the “bit value” by 2 and check if “decimal number” is greater
than or equal to “bit value”.</source>
        <target>crwdns8509:0crwdne8509:0</target>
        <note>Context: XPath: /ul/li[2]/p</note>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="8510" identifier="7b21dffbdb89d6b7231d8ccd67e090e4">
        <source>If it is, play a high note and subtract “bit value” from the “decimal
number”.</source>
        <target>crwdns8510:0crwdne8510:0</target>
        <note>Context: XPath: /ul/li[2]/p</note>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="8511" identifier="149383ce97567f2ef5fd77877588a47e">
        <source>If not, play a low note.</source>
        <target>crwdns8511:0crwdne8511:0</target>
        <note>Context: XPath: /ul/li[2]/p</note>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="8512" identifier="59dd64b7020a1145fec7b7479487c95e">
        <source>Repeat until “bit value” is equal to 1.</source>
        <target>crwdns8512:0crwdne8512:0</target>
        <note>Context: XPath: /ul/li[2]/p</note>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="8513" identifier="4aab632aaf0312192ebad7d6e5661de5">
        <source>To play a musical note use the block
&lt;code&gt;scratch:play note (60 v) for (0.5) beats&lt;/code&gt; beats under the “Sound”.
Type in the number “72” for a high note and “48” for a low note.</source>
        <target>crwdns8513:0crwdne8513:0</target>
        <note>Context: List Item&#13;
XPath: /ul/li[3]</note>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="8514" identifier="ba4527dcb590508d5b6d2387a300191a">
        <source>Test your program with some values on the boundaries (for example test it
with numbers 0 and 31).</source>
        <target>crwdns8514:0crwdne8514:0</target>
        <note>Context: List Item&#13;
XPath: /ul/li[4]</note>
      </trans-unit>
